pe velocity ($500$ km/s). We conclude that quasar-host galaxies at\n$z \\geq 6$ are accreting non-negligible amount of cosmic gas, nevertheless AGN\nfeedback quenches their star formation dominantly by powerful outflows ejecting\ngas out of the host galaxy halo.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Jul 2017 18:47:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-06"}
